    "question_en": "Farmer, what are the primary responsibilities of the National Fertilizer Regulatory Commission (NFRC) in ensuring a stable and effective fertiliser industry in Malawi?",
    "answer_en": "Well, as an extension officer, the NFRC is crucial. It’s essentially the guardian of the fertiliser industry. Its key roles are threefold: firstly, it manages the fertiliser fund – that’s where the fees for registration, levy, inspections, and penalties are all collected. Secondly, it’s responsible for registering and accrediting entities – businesses and individuals involved in fertiliser production, distribution, and use. Finally, it reviews and updates the Fertiliser Act and regulations regularly to keep pace with international standards and ensure they remain effective.  Essentially, it’s about ensuring the industry is well-regulated and operates responsibly."
  },
  {
