    "answer_en": "Absolutely! IPM focuses on a layered approach. You can use resistant varieties – those that are naturally less susceptible to pests – and implement crop rotation to disrupt pest life cycles.  For example, rotating different crops can disrupt the life cycle of pests that are prevalent in your area.  We also use cultural practices like planting at the right time, intercropping (growing different crops together), and using techniques like sanitation to minimize pest populations.  Remember, the goal is to keep pests below levels that cause economic damage."
  },
