    "answer_en": "Well, that’s a common concern with soybean diseases. The symptoms you describe – yellowing, curling, and leaf banding – are often signs of mosaic viruses. They’re typically starting in the early stages of growth.  To prevent this, ensure you’re using certified seed from reputable sources, as those with the virus are often isolated.  Also, planting seeds away from areas where aphids or beetles are prevalent will help reduce the risk of infection.  Early planting is key to establishing healthy plants that are more resistant."
