  {
    "question_en": "How can I effectively control soybean diseases like pod blight and stem blight, especially when they’re already established?",
    "answer_en": "You’re right to be concerned about those diseases!  They’re often difficult to manage.  We need to focus on a multi-pronged approach. Firstly, using resistant soybean varieties is crucial. Secondly, implementing rigorous roguing practices – removing and destroying infected plants – significantly reduces the spread of the disease.  Finally, rotating soybeans with non-host crops like maize or sorghum can help break the cycle of disease transmission.  Don’t use seeds from plants showing symptoms."
  },
